<node id="Compliance">
  <data key="d0">Compliance</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">**Compliance** refers to the adherence to legal, regulatory, and organizational standards that must be met for items, equipment, or inspections within a system. It encompasses legal requirements or standards that items in an inventory system must satisfy, ensuring regulatory adherence and compliance checks are systematically managed. In the context of equipment inspection, compliance involves meeting regulatory or organizational requirements, such as those outlined in standards like DGUV V3 or DGUV Vorschrift 3, which govern industrial safety and maintenance.

As a mandatory field, compliance ensures that equipment, catalogs, or *Betriebsmittel* (operational resources) adhere to applicable norms, whether legal, regulatory, or internal organizational policies. The system autonomously manages compliance for industrial safety and maintenance, verifying that all processes align with established legal and regulatory frameworks to mitigate risks and maintain operational integrity.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-028&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-040&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-031&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-001&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-032&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-043&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-067&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-046&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-024&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-037</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
