<node id="Attribute">
  <data key="d0">Attribute</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The **Attribute** refers to customizable properties or characteristics assigned to equipment, devices, or operational resources to enhance their metadata and enable precise data capture. These attributes can include user-defined fields such as serial numbers, load capacity, length, inspection dates, or other operational details beyond standard data fields. They may be tailored to specific categories of equipment or devices, defining the type of information to be recorded (e.g., text, numeric, date, or select fields).

In the context of **Betriebsmittel** (operational equipment), attributes are custom properties or characteristics that can be linked to entries, populated from external sources like CSV columns, or incremented if marked with a specific flag. Additionally, **Attributes** in Lizard serve as a resource for managing these custom data fields, allowing users to define and organize metadata for items within a catalog. The flexibility of attributes supports diverse use cases, from tracking technical specifications to recording operational metadata.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-028&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-039&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-040&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-063&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-053&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-032&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-025&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-034&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-035&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-058&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-059&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-033</data>
