</node>
<node id="Prüfvorlage">
  <data key="d0">Prüfvorlage</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The **Prüfvorlage** is a predefined template used for conducting standardized inspections, primarily within the Service module. It serves as a configurable framework for creating, editing, or managing inspections, ensuring consistency and compliance across equipment checks. The template includes fields such as name, norms/guidelines, and question catalogs to standardize inspection procedures, and it can be imported, exported, or deleted as needed.

In practical applications, the Prüfvorlage is employed to generate inspection reports, such as PDFs, where recorded working times are displayed for customer transparency. It may also function as an introductory text in a *Prüfauftrag* (inspection order) or as a checklist tailored to the category of equipment being inspected. Additionally, it supports compliance checks by defining predefined criteria for *Prüfungen* (inspections) on *Betriebsmittel* (operational equipment), ensuring adherence to established norms and guidelines.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-060&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-039&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-064&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-044&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-003&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-023&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-024&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-036&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-048&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-027</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356266</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vorlage">
  <data key="d0">Vorlage</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The content of a Textvorlagen entry, which may include placeholders depending on the category, used for standardized communication in inspections and emails.&lt;SEP&gt;Selection field for selecting a template for the inspection result.&lt;SEP&gt;Template used as a base for generating multiple copies in Batch-Import&lt;SEP&gt;Template containing predefined field types (e.g., yes/no, multiple choice) used to standardize inspection processes.&lt;SEP&gt;Template structure consisting of various field types for creating inspection checklists.&lt;SEP&gt;A text template selected for configuring the layout and structure of inspection reports or other documents&lt;SEP&gt;Template used for standardizing roles or processes, grouped into recommended and remaining categories</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-039&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-061&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-010&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-022&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-003&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-023</data>
