  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Katalog">
  <data key="d0">Katalog</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The **Katalog** is a structured system within Lizard designed to organize, manage, and facilitate the import of operational equipment and related data. It serves as a predefined set of fields, attributes, and mappings used in processes like ExpressImport and Batch-Import to structure and standardize imported data before transmission to Lizard. The Katalog functions as a collection of items, assets, or equipment records, which can be created, edited, or deleted, with changes potentially affecting associated data such as inspection templates, Betriebsmittel (operational resources), or Prüfergebnis (inspection results) configurations.

Within the Lizard system, the Katalog acts as a catalog system for organizing operational equipment into categories, enabling structured data management. It supports workflows by allowing the creation and sending of collections of items or resources, which are then referenced in various contexts, including inspection result configurations and Betriebsmittel management. Additionally, the Katalog includes predefined attributes and default values for CSV mapping during import processes, ensuring consistency in data import. Once created or imported via ExpressImport, a Katalog appears in the overview and is ready for batch import, serving as a centralized inventory or database for organizing and managing items or equipment records.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-060&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-039&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-051&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-062&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-030&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-009&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-019&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-010&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-053&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-043&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-044&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-035&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-014&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-015&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-058&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-016</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356267</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Kunde">
  <data key="d0">Kunde</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">An entity whose license quota is checked during item creation, distinct from the master company&lt;SEP&gt;External business entity with which Lizard maintains a relationship&lt;SEP&gt;A customer who signs off on inspection results directly on a tablet or smartphone, completing the inspection process.&lt;SEP&gt;A customer who inspects or manages equipment and signs off on inspection orders.&lt;SEP&gt;Customer or client whose assets are being managed or inspected</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-039&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-061&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-051&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-052&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-044</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356267</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Prüfer">
  <data key="d0">Prüfer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The **Prüfer** is an individual responsible for conducting inspections, audits, or assessments, primarily focused on evaluating equipment, assets, or operational resources. This role involves performing inspections, documenting defects or findings, and recording results based on checklists or system requirements. The Prüfer ensures compliance with operational statuses, such as determining whether equipment is "Betriebsbereit" (operational) or "Gesperrt" (locked/non-operational), and may trigger status changes by locking devices via the application.

In some contexts, the Prüfer is specifically tasked with inspecting *Betriebsmittel* (operational resources) and confirming their operational readiness. The role may also include responsibilities related to time tracking, where the Prüfer records time entries in the system. Additionally, the Prüfer can be filtered or referenced in data displays, collaboration modules, or inspection orders, indicating their involvement in structured workflows. While the core function revolves around inspection and documentation, variations in the role—such as acting as a reviewer, examiner, or technician—suggest a flexible position adaptable to different operational contexts, including fieldwork or customer premises.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-060&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-007&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-050&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-061&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-018&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-051&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-062&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-063&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-042&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-001&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-021&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-023&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-046&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-024&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-057&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-047&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-026&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-058&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-037&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-048&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-038&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-036</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356267</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Token">
  <data key="d0">Token</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Authentication token used by Unternehmen to access and manage inventory and storage data.&lt;SEP&gt;Authentication or session tokens managed within the system, removable via the token management interface.&lt;SEP&gt;A credential used for authentication in the Lizard system, which may expire and require renewal&lt;SEP&gt;A security token used for authentication and access management in the Lizard system.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-039&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-053&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-015</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356267</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Partner">
  <data key="d0">Partner</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The **Partner** entity refers to external organizations, individuals, or collaborators interacting with the Lizard system or associated workflows. It encompasses a broad range of entities, including business partners, customers, subsidiaries, subcontractors, and inspection collaborators, all of which maintain varying levels of access and permissions within the system.

In the context of business operations, a **Partner** represents external companies or entities engaged in collaboration, such as customers, subcontractors, or equipment partners, with details like company names, addresses, and collaboration specifics recorded. These entities may also serve as filter criteria in data displays or workflows, particularly in equipment inspection, maintenance, or asset management processes. Some descriptions emphasize their role in inspection workflows, where they act as clients or collaborators, while others highlight their integration into forms, selection fields, or resource categories within the system.

Additionally, the **Partner** entity includes external users granted limited access to shared items in their Lizard accounts, identifiable by a "Geteilt" symbol. In the context of Lizard Connect’s **Partnerlizenzverwaltung** (Partner License Management), it represents collaborators or external partners whose licenses and related operations are managed. The entity may also be invited via email for cooperation, further expanding its scope to include external individuals or organizations participating in collaborative efforts.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-060&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-061&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-062&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-052&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-063&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-020&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-021&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-054&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-055&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-034&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-066&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-045&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-003&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-057&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-047&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-026&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-037&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-059&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-049</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356267</data>
