<node id="Batch-Import">
  <data key="d0">Batch-Import</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The **Batch-Import** process is a method for generating and transferring multiple items or assets collectively to the Lizard system. It involves creating identical entries with increment-based serial numbers, as opposed to the CSV-Import method, which handles unique values. The process includes copy generation, increment logic, and the collective sending of batches, ensuring efficient bulk operations.

Batch-Import is designed for bulk importing, incorporating error handling and rate limiting to manage large volumes of data. It is referenced in the Prüfergebnis function, indicating its role in batch processing workflows. The process specifically facilitates the simultaneous import of multiple *Betriebsmittel* (operational resources or assets) from a template, streamlining the transfer of generated items to Lizard in a single operation.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-039&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-040&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-062&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-009&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-010&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-043&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-014&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-057</data>
