<node id="Techniker">
  <data key="d0">Techniker</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The **Techniker** role encompasses multiple responsibilities related to inspections, maintenance, and data management, primarily through digital tools. In one context, Techniker refers to field technicians who conduct on-site inspections and maintenance tasks using mobile or web applications, such as the Lizard system, Einsatzplaner, or Lizard Connect App. These individuals manage assignments, perform checks, and may answer questions directly within the app, ensuring efficient task execution and data accuracy. Their role often involves hands-on technical work, including manual data entry into systems when required.

In another context, the Techniker role is defined as a user with read-only access to assigned appointments, primarily for informational purposes rather than active task performance. This distinction highlights two distinct functions within the broader Techniker designation: active field technicians performing inspections and maintenance, and administrative or oversight roles focused on reviewing scheduled tasks without direct intervention. The role may also involve manual data entry into systems, further emphasizing its technical and operational dimensions.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-007&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-053&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-044&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-022&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-023&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-067&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-047&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-048&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-006&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-036</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356271</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="App">
  <data key="d0">App</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The **App** is a software application designed for inspection and maintenance workflows, primarily used by technicians and examiners. It functions as a mobile or desktop application, enabling users to manage inspections, scan QR codes, and interact with LizardPro devices. The app requires Bluetooth and location access for NFC tag scanning and resource management, including DynTags. It serves as an interface for the Lizard system, facilitating asset scanning, linking, and documentation of findings. The application supports inspection orders, equipment scanning, and workflow documentation, catering to both mobile and web platforms. Broadly, it is a general-purpose software application associated with Lizard services.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-007&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-008&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-062&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-041&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-053&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-023&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-057&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-016&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-048</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356272</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gültig bis">
  <data key="d0">Gültig bis</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">**Gültig bis** refers to a field or criterion used to indicate the expiration date or validity period of various items, certifications, licenses, or inspections. It serves as a date-based filter in systems like Lizard Connect to identify items or licenses that are valid until a specific date.

The term is applied across multiple contexts, including qualifications, inspections, operational compliance (Betriebsmittel), certifications, and software or employee-related licenses. In each case, **Gültig bis** marks the end of a validity period, allowing users to track soon-to-expire results or ensure ongoing compliance. The field may be stored as a text-based date or integrated as a date range filter, depending on the system’s requirements. Its primary function is to facilitate the monitoring of expiration dates to prevent lapses in validity.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-050&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-061&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-062&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-064&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-043&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-054&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-055&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-034&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-047&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-026</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356273</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
