<node id="ExpressImport">
  <data key="d0">ExpressImport</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">ExpressImport is a software tool or system designed for importing and processing batches of data or documents, particularly within the Lizard asset management ecosystem. It functions primarily within the browser, storing catalogs, items, tokens, and document files locally using technologies like localStorage and IndexedDB without retaining data on the server side. The tool supports various import functionalities, including CSV data parsing, mapping, and batch operations, while adhering to a rate limit of 500 requests per minute to prevent errors.

ExpressImport includes features for automating data standardization, such as removing URL prefixes from CSV values during Dyntag-Mapping to ensure consistent tag formats. It also provides automated suggestions for mapping CSV columns to field names, streamlining the import process. The system enforces security measures by verifying MIME types and file headers during file uploads and handles drag-and-drop functionality for file imports. Additionally, it supports the import of Betriebsmittel (equipment) and related data, as well as the translation of Lizard attribute types into input fields.

The tool is capable of importing catalogs, items, Dyntags, inspection results, and roles or templates, with batch processing capabilities and increment logic for data management. However, its functionality is limited in private or incognito mode. ExpressImport aborts processing upon encountering inconsistent datasets, requiring corrections before re-importing. It is specifically used within the LISS-Engine for creating items from structured data sources and within Lizard for linking Dyntag IDs to positions automatically during inspection result imports. If attributes are updated, the system may require reloading to reflect changes.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-061&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-040&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-051&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-062&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-009&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-019&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-031&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-010&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-053&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-002&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-034&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-013&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-023&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-035&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-014&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-057&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-015&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-047&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-058&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-016&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-027&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-043</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
