  <data key="d2">A speaking column name in Excel used for asset catalog fields, representing the serial number of an asset.&lt;SEP&gt;German term for serial number, used as an attribute in CSV imports for identifying items.&lt;SEP&gt;Serial number attribute of an asset that can be edited by partners but not deleted or archived.&lt;SEP&gt;A unique identifier assigned to Betriebsmittel for tracking and compliance purposes&lt;SEP&gt;A unique identifier for equipment, often used in inventory and inspection reports&lt;SEP&gt;A unique identifier within a document or dataset, often verified for correct extraction by AI.&lt;SEP&gt;A unique identifier assigned to Betriebsmittel for tracking and inventory purposes.</data>
