<node id="NFC">
  <data key="d0">NFC</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Near Field Communication (NFC) is a contactless data transfer technology designed for robust device identification and local data association. It enables the scanning of tags either internally via smartphones or externally through dedicated readers, facilitating efficient interaction with equipment data. NFC is particularly effective in dirty or harsh environments, making it suitable for industrial or field applications where contactless operation is essential.

In the context of the Lizard-App, NFC is utilized for local data association by caching equipment data, allowing seamless integration with mobile devices. Similarly, Lizard Connect supports NFC for interacting with tags, enhancing its role in equipment inspection and data retrieval. The technology’s versatility extends to scanning equipment tags via mobile devices, ensuring reliable performance in challenging conditions. Overall, NFC serves as a dependable solution for contactless tag scanning and data transfer, combining durability with operational flexibility.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-040&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-018&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-041&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-054&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-022&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-034&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-037&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-048</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356277</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
