<node id="Batch">
  <data key="d0">Batch</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">A **Batch** refers to a group of items, documents, data, or positions that are processed, transferred, or reviewed together as part of a workflow or system. In the context of data management, a batch can represent a collection of records or items compiled for import, compliance checks, or AI processing, often allowing for review before finalization and publication. This grouping facilitates efficient handling, enabling batch processing where multiple entries are managed simultaneously rather than individually.

In inventory and data systems, a batch may function as a temporary or intermediate collection, such as one processed before being transferred to another system like Lizard. Batch processing can also involve manual corrections, where errors in individual items do not halt the entire process, and corrections contribute to improving the AI learning system. The concept emphasizes cohesion in data handling, ensuring that related items are grouped for streamlined operations, whether for review, transfer, or compliance purposes.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-040&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-062&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-031&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-053&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-067&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-046&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-004&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-058&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-016&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-059&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-034</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356277</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="IndexedDB">
  <data key="d0">IndexedDB</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">**IndexedDB** is a client-side storage API designed for web applications, enabling the storage of larger amounts of structured data directly within a user's browser. It serves as a browser-based database system with significantly higher storage limits—ranging from hundreds of megabytes to gigabytes—allocated proportionally to the browser's available quota. Unlike `localStorage`, IndexedDB stores data asynchronously and separately, allowing for more efficient handling of larger datasets, including document files, invoice files, and inspection results.

In the context of **ExpressImport**, IndexedDB functions as a browser-based storage mechanism for catalogs, items, tokens, and document files, facilitating local data persistence. It also stores audit file results and uploaded files independently from `localStorage`, ensuring separation of concerns. However, IndexedDB data is cleared when an incognito window is closed, which may impact temporary storage needs. Additionally, its capacity to store structured data may trigger full storage warnings in some applications, reflecting its role as a robust but capacity-conscious client-side database solution.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-062&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-042&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-043&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-013&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-023&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-014&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-015&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-016&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-027</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356279</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="localStorage">
  <data key="d0">localStorage</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">**localStorage** is a browser-based storage mechanism primarily utilized by ExpressImport for storing various types of data locally within a user's browser. It serves as a client-side storage solution for catalogs, items, tokens, document files, mappings, and application settings, enabling temporary data retention across web sessions. The storage operates under a domain-specific hard limit of approximately 5 MB, restricting the volume of data that can be stored per domain to prevent excessive resource consumption.

This mechanism is designed for temporary data storage, with its contents cleared automatically when the browser operates in incognito or private mode, ensuring privacy by erasing stored data upon session termination. As part of the Web Storage API, localStorage functions as a key-value store, providing web applications with a straightforward method for persisting small amounts of data directly within the client environment. Its usage is context-dependent, often tied to specific applications like ExpressImport, where it supports functionalities such as catalog management and session token retention.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-062&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-042&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-013&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-023&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-014&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-016&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-027</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356279</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Benutzer">
  <data key="d0">Benutzer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The term **Benutzer** refers to individuals or entities that interact with the Lizard Pro system or platform, encompassing a broad range of roles and contexts. In its most general sense, a Benutzer is any user who engages with the system for operational purposes, whether internal or external to the organization. This includes employees, external auditors, and other stakeholders who require access to manage settings, resources, or perform system-related tasks.

Within the Lizard system, a Benutzer is formally defined as a user account with assigned roles and permissions, facilitating controlled access to specific functionalities and data. The term also extends to colleagues or users within an organization, particularly in contexts involving multi-user selection or collaborative workflows. Additionally, Benutzer can represent a resource within Lizard dedicated to managing user accounts, profiles, and access rights, ensuring secure and organized administration of system interactions.

Overall, the concept of Benutzer is multifaceted, serving as both an active participant in system operations and a managed entity within the platform’s governance framework.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-062&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-043&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-044&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-005&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-016&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-027&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-059</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356279</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Betriebsmittelnummer">
  <data key="d0">Betriebsmittelnummer</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The **Betriebsmittelnummer** is a unique identifier assigned to *Betriebsmittel* (operating resources or equipment/assets) within a system. It serves as a distinct reference for tracking, cataloging, and managing individual equipment positions, ensuring each asset can be uniquely identified and referenced in various records, including detail views and Prüfungen (inspections).

In some contexts, particularly when operating in CSV mode, the Betriebsmittelnummer may be optional and derived from a mapped CSV column. When applicable, it often follows an increment logic, especially when an increment flag is set in the catalog, ensuring sequential numbering for related assets. The identifier is commonly structured as a combination of an inventory number and a sequential number (e.g., 27123-011), providing a standardized format for clear differentiation between assets. Across all descriptions, the Betriebsmittelnummer consistently functions as a unique, system-wide reference for equipment or assets, facilitating organized tracking and operational management.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-051&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-019&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-064&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-025&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-043&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-034&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-035&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-024</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356280</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="PDF">
  <data key="d0">PDF</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">**Portable Document Format (PDF)**

The Portable Document Format (PDF) is a versatile file format primarily used for document exchange, storage, and processing across various contexts. It serves as a standardized means to return inspection results from service providers to operators, often in the form of generated documents that summarize findings or orders. These documents can be regenerated or exported as needed, ensuring flexibility in handling inspection-related data.

PDF files are widely utilized for unstructured data input and processing, including scanned reports, invoices, delivery notes, certificates, and inspection reports. They are also employed for uploading attachments, such as Prüfergebnis (inspection results) or Prüfberichte (test reports), particularly when linked to Betriebsmittel (equipment or assets). Additionally, PDFs facilitate document preview and output, making them a practical choice for both digital and physical record-keeping. The format supports the storage and sharing of structured or semi-structured data, including Betriebsmittel data imports, ensuring compatibility across different systems and workflows.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-030&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-042&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-020&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-043&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-021&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-023&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-057&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-006&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-014</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356280</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mitarbeiter">
  <data key="d0">Mitarbeiter</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The **Mitarbeiter** (employee) refers to an individual within an organizational or system context, encompassing various roles and responsibilities related to qualifications, equipment management, and operational tasks. As an employee, they are responsible for interacting with the **Zeiterfassung** system to document time intervals for inspection orders, including opening, working on, starting, and stopping tasks. Within the **Lizard platform**, a Mitarbeiter is represented as a user account with associated roles, licenses, and permissions, serving as a resource category for managing employee-related data such as profiles and certifications.

Mitarbeiter are linked to qualifications and items, with their expertise and credentials managed and verified by the system. They may hold specific qualifications required for tasks, certifications, or equipment management, ensuring compliance with operational standards. Some Mitarbeiter are designated as responsible for equipment inspection or maintenance, while others are tasked with managing licenses, equipment, or system-related functions. Additionally, employees from service companies may require system access and role assignments to perform their duties effectively.

The system maintains detailed records of Mitarbeiter, including their names, emails, roles, license statuses, and qualifications, ensuring accountability and efficient resource allocation. Their responsibilities may extend to operating or overseeing **Betriebsmittel** (operational equipment), further integrating them into the workflow of maintenance and inspection processes.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-063&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-064&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-025&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-011&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-003&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-023&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-046&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-004&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-047&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-005&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-037&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-059&lt;SEP&gt;doc-fb57212021fb1e5e7a76ae882be19321-chunk-038</data>
  <data key="d4">LizardDocu.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1781356280</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
